.TH _printf 3 "April 2026" "C - printf" "User Functions"
.SH NAME
_printf \- custom printf function
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include "main.h"
.PP
.B int _printf(const char *format, ...);
.SH DESCRIPTION
The _printf function prints output according to a format string.

It writes output to the standard output.

Supported format specifiers:
.TP
.B %c
Prints a character.
.TP
.B %s
Prints a string.
.TP
.B %%
Prints a percent sign.
.TP
.B %d
Prints an integer.
.TP
.B %i
Prints an integer.
.SH RETURN VALUE
The _printf function returns the number of characters printed.

If an error happens, it returns -1.
